    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Montreal</placeName>
                <date>5 September<add>?</add> 1860</date>
            </p>
            <p>My dear <addressee>Mr Leeser</addressee></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">My sister mentioned to me in her<lb/> return from the states
                    <del>that</del> you were much surprised<lb/> that you had not reced any account
                of the annual<lb/> Election of officers to our small congregation, to<lb/> make up
                therefore for much remisness I now send<lb/> you the names of those elected at
                our<lb/> meeting and also an account of <persName>Mr DeSola's</persName><lb/>
                <add>?</add> interesting lecture on the Persecution<lb/> our <sic>bretheren</sic>
                are suffering in the dominions<lb/> of the <persName>Shah</persName><add>?</add>.
                You will find some corrections<lb/> in the printed a/c of the lecture which I<lb/>
                hope you will understand.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I took no notes of the lecture &amp; have not<lb/> read it since but
                I think what I have<lb/> written <add>?</add> to be quite sufficient for
                publication<lb/> in a journal devoted to Jewish affairs</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>I may, however mention in <add>?</add> to <persName>Mr DeSola</persName><lb/> the
                lecture was got up at a very short notice<lb/> &amp; being addressed to a mixed
                audience <del>was</del><lb/> became a difficult subject—he however<lb/> acquitted
                himself with his usual ability<lb/> &amp; has acquired some reputation from it.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">It has caused quite a sensation<lb/> among 'the clergy' here &amp;
                the messenger<lb/> sincerely<add>?</add> has a good deal thought of from<lb/> being
                the first Eastern who has <add>?</add><lb/> these northern shores.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I should like <del>you</del> to insert the<lb/> account of the
                lecture as from a friend<lb/> without putting any signature to the<lb/>
                communication as my writings are generally<lb/> confined to professional &amp; not
                religious<lb/> subjects. Yours very sincerely</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <persName role="author">A H David</persName>
            </p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p rend="Text written sideways on this page"/>
            <p>At the annual meeting of the congregation the following<lb/> gentlemen were elected
                to serve during the present year<lb/>
                <persName>Mr. S. David</persName> President. <persName>Goodman Benjamin</persName>
                Leadr <persName>William<lb/> Benjamin</persName> Secty &amp; <persName>Myer
                    Solomons</persName>
                <persName>G. I. Ascher</persName> &amp; <persName>Dr David</persName><lb/> Trustees.
                And at the first meeting of the Trustees<lb/>
                <persName>Dr David</persName> was elected Parnass</p>
        </body>
